1. **Precision**: Each bounding box should perfectly enclose one single target object. In this image, both bounding boxes correctly enclose one tower crane each. The bounding boxes do not include any other objects.
2. **Recall**: All target objects should be localized by a bounding box. In this image, there are two tower cranes, and both are localized by bounding boxes.
3. **Fit**: Each bounding box should neither be too loose nor too tight. The bounding boxes are reasonably well-fitted to the tower cranes. They are not excessively loose or tight, and they reasonably estimate the size of the cranes, even if parts are occluded.
